infinite loop is a loop that continues to execute indefinitely because the loop's terminating condition is never met. This can lead to a program becoming unresponsive or crashing if not handled properly. It's important to ensure that loops have a clear exit condition to prevent infinite loops.
Example of an infinite loop using a while loop
while (true) {
    console.log("This loop will run forever!");
}

while loop in javascript
that is used to execute a block of code as long as a specified condition is true. 
The syntax of a while loop is as follows:
while (condition) {
    // code to be executed
}    
Example of a while loop that prints the numbers from 1 to 5
let count = 1;
while (count <= 5) {
    console.log(count);
    count++;
}    
Example of a while loop that calculates the factorial of a number
let number = 5;
let factorial = 1;
while (number > 0) {
    factorial *= number;
    number--;
}
console.log("Factorial:", factorial);



